This paper deals with the problem of secure and private distributed matrix multiplication, which involves cryptography and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the tradeoff between upload and download costs, which is a topic in information theory, making cs.IT (Information Theory) another likely sub-category. The problem of distributed matrix multiplication involves distributed computing, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also uses ideas from secret sharing and coded private information retrieval, which are topics in cryptography and coding theory, respectively, making cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) possible sub-categories as well.
